WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.972 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.972 --> 00:00:17.465 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:17.465 --> 00:03:10.680 align:middle line:90%


00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:14.200 align:middle line:84%
>>We who solve mystery,
become mystery.

00:03:14.200 --> 00:03:17.170 align:middle line:84%
Our chemical wisdom handed
down through the ages,

00:03:17.170 --> 00:03:19.970 align:middle line:84%
and now graffiti in the
sterile men's toilets

00:03:19.970 --> 00:03:21.930 align:middle line:90%
at the Lima airport.

00:03:21.930 --> 00:03:24.081 align:middle line:84%
Scrolled, no doubt,
by one of the tourists

00:03:24.081 --> 00:03:25.330 align:middle line:90%
waiting out in the food court.

00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:28.290 align:middle line:90%


00:03:28.290 --> 00:03:31.020 align:middle line:84%
Outside, milling under
the ubiquitous gaze

00:03:31.020 --> 00:03:34.560 align:middle line:84%
of security cameras, the
colorful new-age souls,

00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:37.030 align:middle line:84%
middle-aged academics,
and passengers

00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:40.490 align:middle line:84%
that give you that odd
conspiratorial smile that says,

00:03:40.490 --> 00:03:41.490 align:middle line:90%
yes.

00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:43.810 align:middle line:84%
We're here for the
shaman conference.

00:03:43.810 --> 00:03:47.760 align:middle line:84%
And here we are, chowing down
on McDonald's and Donut King,

00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:50.280 align:middle line:84%
getting our last
hits of civilization

00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:53.718 align:middle line:84%
before hitting the jungle city
of Iquitos and shamanic boot

00:03:53.718 --> 00:03:54.218 align:middle line:90%
camp.

00:03:54.218 --> 00:03:59.280 align:middle line:90%


00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:03.350 align:middle line:84%
It feels like some whacked
out reality TV show.

00:04:03.350 --> 00:04:07.330 align:middle line:84%
The generational snapshot
of a new psychedelic wave

00:04:07.330 --> 00:04:09.460 align:middle line:90%
just before it breaks.

00:04:09.460 --> 00:04:11.980 align:middle line:84%
Bright-eyed Westerners
about to die

00:04:11.980 --> 00:04:15.930 align:middle line:84%
and be reborn in the humid
jungles of Peru, drinking

00:04:15.930 --> 00:04:18.010 align:middle line:84%
their hallucinogenic
brew, ayahuasca.

00:04:18.010 --> 00:04:25.124 align:middle line:90%


00:04:25.124 --> 00:04:26.540 align:middle line:84%
Ayahuasca is a
plant medicine that

00:04:26.540 --> 00:04:28.720 align:middle line:84%
has been used by the
indigenous people of South

00:04:28.720 --> 00:04:32.570 align:middle line:84%
America for millennia to
heal physical ailments

00:04:32.570 --> 00:04:37.630 align:middle line:84%
and, they claim, to cleanse
and purify the spirit.

00:04:37.630 --> 00:04:40.690 align:middle line:84%
It was discovered
by the West in 1851,

00:04:40.690 --> 00:04:42.850 align:middle line:84%
when the legendary
British botanist Richard

00:04:42.850 --> 00:04:46.080 align:middle line:84%
Spruce explored
the Rio Negro basin

00:04:46.080 --> 00:04:50.240 align:middle line:84%
and was introduced to the
vine by the Tukanoan Indians.

00:04:50.240 --> 00:04:52.980 align:middle line:84%
Spruce gave the vine
its scientific name,

00:04:52.980 --> 00:04:55.550 align:middle line:90%
Banisteriopsis Caapi.

00:04:55.550 --> 00:04:57.950 align:middle line:10%
In different areas
of South America,

00:04:57.950 --> 00:05:02.430 align:middle line:10%
it is also known
as yage or hoasca.

00:05:02.430 --> 00:05:04.900 align:middle line:10%
For a while in the
mid-20th century,

00:05:04.900 --> 00:05:08.190 align:middle line:10%
chemists who isolated the
active properties of the vine

00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:10.000 align:middle line:10%
called their
compound telepathine.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:12.610 align:middle line:10%


00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:16.450 align:middle line:10%
Research showed it contained
various harmala alkaloids,

00:05:16.450 --> 00:05:18.340 align:middle line:10%
which are then
boiled up in a brew,

00:05:18.340 --> 00:05:22.400 align:middle line:10%
also called ayahuasca, with
a multitude of other plants,

00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:26.230 align:middle line:10%
one being the leafy Psychotria
Viridis, which contains

00:05:26.230 --> 00:05:30.760 align:middle line:10%
the powerful hallucinogenic
chemical, Dimethyltryptamine,

00:05:30.760 --> 00:05:33.930 align:middle line:10%
also known as DMT.

00:05:33.930 --> 00:05:36.340 align:middle line:84%
On its own, the
vine is only orally

00:05:36.340 --> 00:05:38.550 align:middle line:90%
active at very high doses.

00:05:38.550 --> 00:05:43.750 align:middle line:84%
But it does contain potent MAO
monoamine oxidase inhibitors

00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:46.430 align:middle line:84%
that overpower the
body's own enzymes

00:05:46.430 --> 00:05:50.240 align:middle line:90%
and allow the DMT to potentiate.

00:05:50.240 --> 00:05:53.590 align:middle line:84%
Science has made cautious
forays into the jungle

00:05:53.590 --> 00:05:56.090 align:middle line:84%
to study the vine in
its native setting.

00:05:56.090 --> 00:05:59.820 align:middle line:10%
Or, as with the Huasca
Project in the 1990s,

00:05:59.820 --> 00:06:01.530 align:middle line:10%
to study church
members of groups

00:06:01.530 --> 00:06:05.930 align:middle line:10%
like the UDV, who
Ayahuasca as part

00:06:05.930 --> 00:06:10.200 align:middle line:10%
of their synchratic
Christian jungle religion.

00:06:10.200 --> 00:06:13.700 align:middle line:84%
What they found was that
regular ayahuasca use flushed

00:06:13.700 --> 00:06:17.080 align:middle line:84%
the brain clean and
improved receptor sites,

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:21.390 align:middle line:84%
suggesting the vine could
be a medicinal goldmine.

00:06:21.390 --> 00:06:25.380 align:middle line:84%
But what science cannot explain
is the psychic effect of this

00:06:25.380 --> 00:06:28.495 align:middle line:84%
mother of all plants--
the sense of the numinous

00:06:28.495 --> 00:06:33.510 align:middle line:84%
and the spiritual world
it reportedly opens up.

00:06:33.510 --> 00:06:38.240 align:middle line:84%
Those who drink say that each
ayahuasca journey is unique.

00:06:38.240 --> 00:06:40.860 align:middle line:84%
The spirit of the
vine comes alive.

00:06:40.860 --> 00:06:42.900 align:middle line:90%
It guides and teaches.

00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:46.186 align:middle line:84%
And on the other side,
nothing is ever the same.

00:06:46.186 --> 00:06:47.285 align:middle line:90%
Or so they say.

00:06:47.285 --> 00:06:51.550 align:middle line:90%


00:06:51.550 --> 00:06:53.470 align:middle line:10%
The native men and
women who safeguard

00:06:53.470 --> 00:06:55.660 align:middle line:10%
the knowledge of the
vine, and of the spirits

00:06:55.660 --> 00:07:00.190 align:middle line:10%
it is said to reveal, are the
curanderos and the curanderas.

00:07:00.190 --> 00:07:04.280 align:middle line:10%
Or as the West would
call them, shaman.

00:07:04.280 --> 00:07:07.720 align:middle line:10%
Their role has been that of
healer, priest, and traveler

00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:10.770 align:middle line:10%
between worlds, acting
as intermediaries

00:07:10.770 --> 00:07:13.310 align:middle line:10%
between the spiritual
dimension and this world,

00:07:13.310 --> 00:07:14.840 align:middle line:10%
on behalf of their patients.

00:07:14.840 --> 00:07:17.530 align:middle line:90%


00:07:17.530 --> 00:07:21.320 align:middle line:84%
Yet the demands of the work and
the rise of Western materialism

00:07:21.320 --> 00:07:23.950 align:middle line:84%
throughout South
America have seen a fall

00:07:23.950 --> 00:07:28.050 align:middle line:84%
in prestige and customers
for the curanderos.

00:07:28.050 --> 00:07:30.710 align:middle line:84%
The profession,
usually hereditary,

00:07:30.710 --> 00:07:34.330 align:middle line:84%
was in danger of extinction
before an unprecedented wave

00:07:34.330 --> 00:07:38.350 align:middle line:84%
of Western gringos started
coming in search of ayahuasca

00:07:38.350 --> 00:07:41.990 align:middle line:90%
and the healing it can provide.

00:07:41.990 --> 00:07:46.240 align:middle line:84%
Over the last 20 years or
so, a new gringo trail,

00:07:46.240 --> 00:07:48.660 align:middle line:84%
this one a journey
of the soul, has

00:07:48.660 --> 00:07:52.110 align:middle line:84%
been blossoming in the
jungles of South America.

00:07:52.110 --> 00:07:54.880 align:middle line:84%
Seekers and thrill
seekers alike have

00:07:54.880 --> 00:07:58.210 align:middle line:84%
been coming from the West for
a reconnection to the deeper

00:07:58.210 --> 00:08:01.020 align:middle line:84%
reality shamanism
connects one to,

00:08:01.020 --> 00:08:02.790 align:middle line:84%
and bringing back
amazing stories

00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:07.400 align:middle line:84%
of hallucinogenic trips,
healing and enlightenment.

00:08:07.400 --> 00:08:10.540 align:middle line:84%
Indigenous shamanism has quickly
become the most profitable

00:08:10.540 --> 00:08:14.440 align:middle line:84%
business in town, and numerous
jungle lodges and retreats

00:08:14.440 --> 00:08:16.640 align:middle line:84%
have sprung up
across South America

00:08:16.640 --> 00:08:20.250 align:middle line:84%
to cater to the influx
of rich tourists.

00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:22.570 align:middle line:84%
This has spilled over
onto the internet,

00:08:22.570 --> 00:08:24.580 align:middle line:84%
as hundreds of
ayahuasca websites,

00:08:24.580 --> 00:08:27.050 align:middle line:84%
chat rooms and
forums have emerged

00:08:27.050 --> 00:08:29.840 align:middle line:84%
to crystallize a
global subculture

00:08:29.840 --> 00:08:32.770 align:middle line:84%
engaging with an indigenous
spiritual practice,

00:08:32.770 --> 00:08:34.990 align:middle line:84%
and ceding it back
to the Western world.

00:08:34.990 --> 00:08:39.150 align:middle line:90%


00:08:39.150 --> 00:08:43.059 align:middle line:84%
And here I was, a 36-year-old
freelance journalist,

00:08:43.059 --> 00:08:45.290 align:middle line:84%
reporting on an
academic style gathering

00:08:45.290 --> 00:08:47.170 align:middle line:90%
with a pronounced twist.

00:08:47.170 --> 00:08:49.740 align:middle line:84%
It was all about
Amazonian shamanism,

00:08:49.740 --> 00:08:52.260 align:middle line:90%
with a hands-on component.

00:08:52.260 --> 00:08:56.060 align:middle line:10%
With its entrepreneurial blend
of spirituality and capitalism,

00:08:56.060 --> 00:08:58.750 align:middle line:10%
the Second Amazonian
Shaman Conference

00:08:58.750 --> 00:09:01.750 align:middle line:10%
may be the perfect
mix of paradigms.

00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:05.570 align:middle line:10%
It bills itself as a gathering
of curanderos, scientists

00:09:05.570 --> 00:09:07.710 align:middle line:10%
and interested members
of the public who

00:09:07.710 --> 00:09:09.670 align:middle line:10%
have a yearning for
indigenous spirituality.

00:09:09.670 --> 00:09:14.080 align:middle line:90%


00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:17.200 align:middle line:10%
Kevin is a long-haired
gringo from San Francisco,

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:21.820 align:middle line:10%
in his late 30s, with angelic
good looks and hazel eyes.

00:09:21.820 --> 00:09:23.800 align:middle line:10%
He's been wandering
the world and learning

00:09:23.800 --> 00:09:26.930 align:middle line:10%
about indigenous medicines
for over a decade.

00:09:26.930 --> 00:09:29.860 align:middle line:84%
Training for two years
in an intensive dieta

00:09:29.860 --> 00:09:34.210 align:middle line:84%
with medicinal plants at the
famed Sachamama Ethnobotanical

00:09:34.210 --> 00:09:37.970 align:middle line:90%
Gardens outside Iquitos.

00:09:37.970 --> 00:09:41.090 align:middle line:84%
Kevin had followed through
on the shaman's path

00:09:41.090 --> 00:09:44.480 align:middle line:84%
that I and ayahuasca
seekers like me were just

00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:46.340 align:middle line:90%
beginning to tread.

00:09:46.340 --> 00:09:49.420 align:middle line:84%
He was a seed brother,
and in his example,

00:09:49.420 --> 00:09:53.000 align:middle line:84%
there was a burning promise that
if he could bridge the worlds,

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:54.450 align:middle line:90%
we all could.

00:09:54.450 --> 00:09:58.100 align:middle line:84%
The cultural firewall that kept
the shamanic reality separate

00:09:58.100 --> 00:10:01.300 align:middle line:90%
from the west could be lifted.

00:10:01.300 --> 00:10:04.830 align:middle line:10%
>>In this Amazonian
system, human beings

00:10:04.830 --> 00:10:06.910 align:middle line:10%
are trained by the
higher energetic selves

00:10:06.910 --> 00:10:08.610 align:middle line:10%
of plants and trees.

00:10:08.610 --> 00:10:11.540 align:middle line:10%
As they enter this
process, this process

00:10:11.540 --> 00:10:13.520 align:middle line:10%
of shamanic initiation,
if you will,

00:10:13.520 --> 00:10:16.280 align:middle line:10%
in the Amazonian system,
basically, the higher

00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:19.560 align:middle line:10%
energetic selves, the spirits,
if you will, of the plants

00:10:19.560 --> 00:10:22.370 align:middle line:10%
enter into an agreement,
a relationship

00:10:22.370 --> 00:10:25.010 align:middle line:10%
with the student,
the human student.

00:10:25.010 --> 00:10:26.340 align:middle line:90%
They work on a physical level.

00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:28.230 align:middle line:84%
We have a physical
body, but we also

00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:32.840 align:middle line:84%
have energetic bodies
associated with the seven

00:10:32.840 --> 00:10:35.060 align:middle line:90%
major chakras in our body.

00:10:35.060 --> 00:10:38.480 align:middle line:84%
So on an energetic level, the
higher energetic substances,

00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:41.960 align:middle line:84%
the spirits of the plants,
come and they heal us.

00:10:41.960 --> 00:10:45.070 align:middle line:90%
They remove blockages.

00:10:45.070 --> 00:10:47.800 align:middle line:84%
They clean our
soul, if you will.

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:50.390 align:middle line:90%
They also prepare us.

00:10:50.390 --> 00:10:54.660 align:middle line:84%
They organize the lines of
energy, the rivers of light

00:10:54.660 --> 00:10:57.640 align:middle line:90%
that flow through our body.

00:10:57.640 --> 00:10:59.760 align:middle line:90%
They untangle these lines.

00:10:59.760 --> 00:11:03.150 align:middle line:84%
And then they help to open
up the center so that we

00:11:03.150 --> 00:11:06.350 align:middle line:90%
have different abilities.

00:11:06.350 --> 00:11:09.132 align:middle line:84%
For instance, the ability
to talk to plants and trees,

00:11:09.132 --> 00:11:12.370 align:middle line:84%
or to see different
vibrational dimensions.

00:11:12.370 --> 00:11:19.470 align:middle line:90%


00:11:19.470 --> 00:11:22.090 align:middle line:84%
>>Strange to think that
in the first decade

00:11:22.090 --> 00:11:26.120 align:middle line:84%
of the 21st century, I'll be
heading to the Peruvian jungle

00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:29.020 align:middle line:84%
in search of a connection
to the primal consciousness

00:11:29.020 --> 00:11:31.490 align:middle line:90%
that indigenous wisdom revealed.

00:11:31.490 --> 00:11:36.040 align:middle line:84%
Yet in a world of global warming
and environmental collapse,

00:11:36.040 --> 00:11:38.190 align:middle line:84%
it seemed all the more
urgent to reconnect

00:11:38.190 --> 00:11:41.110 align:middle line:84%
with the planet
in a visceral way.

00:11:41.110 --> 00:11:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Now days, we are all
part of the story.

00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.940 align:middle line:84%
And getting down and
dirty in the far crevices

00:11:45.940 --> 00:11:48.640 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness was a
prospect I was relishing.

00:11:48.640 --> 00:11:51.470 align:middle line:90%


00:11:51.470 --> 00:11:53.630 align:middle line:10%
But what was the
business of spirituality

00:11:53.630 --> 00:11:55.860 align:middle line:10%
doing to all these
backpacking ayahuasca

00:11:55.860 --> 00:12:00.390 align:middle line:10%
seekers that dared to journey
into the mysteries of creation?

00:12:00.390 --> 00:12:03.350 align:middle line:10%
And what did it say about
the growing Western need

00:12:03.350 --> 00:12:07.510 align:middle line:10%
for an authentic
reconnection to the planet?

00:12:07.510 --> 00:12:09.290 align:middle line:90%
Ayahuasca was a mystery to me.

00:12:09.290 --> 00:12:12.030 align:middle line:84%
And I got the feeling that
many of the ayahuasca seekers

00:12:12.030 --> 00:12:14.050 align:middle line:90%
were in the same boat.

00:12:14.050 --> 00:12:17.430 align:middle line:84%
We were all chasing the root of
the vine, eager for the secret

00:12:17.430 --> 00:12:18.960 align:middle line:90%
she might provide.

00:12:18.960 --> 00:12:20.880 align:middle line:84%
But like children in
the ways of the spirit.

00:12:20.880 --> 00:12:23.910 align:middle line:90%


00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:27.280 align:middle line:84%
The ayahuasca network
appears to cut across race,

00:12:27.280 --> 00:12:29.090 align:middle line:90%
social class and gender.

00:12:29.090 --> 00:12:31.820 align:middle line:84%
A secret society
of plant worshipers

00:12:31.820 --> 00:12:34.290 align:middle line:84%
all united by the
common experience

00:12:34.290 --> 00:12:37.060 align:middle line:90%
of this potent hallucinogenic.

00:12:37.060 --> 00:12:39.250 align:middle line:84%
And through them,
the ayahuasca vine

00:12:39.250 --> 00:12:41.880 align:middle line:84%
was spreading her
tendrils across the world.

00:12:41.880 --> 00:12:45.840 align:middle line:84%
And a genuine archaic
revival was underway.

00:12:45.840 --> 00:12:47.310 align:middle line:90%
My bags were packed.

00:12:47.310 --> 00:12:48.830 align:middle line:90%
The jungle beckoned.

00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:52.470 align:middle line:84%
And the ancient mystery of
the rain-forest awaited.

00:12:52.470 --> 00:12:55.228 align:middle line:90%
I wanted in on it.

00:12:55.228 --> 00:12:58.630 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:12:58.630 --> 00:13:04.966 align:middle line:90%


00:13:04.966 --> 00:13:07.070 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE SINGING]

00:13:07.070 --> 00:13:39.990 align:middle line:90%


00:13:39.990 --> 00:13:44.366 align:middle line:84%
The trail is alive with the
sound of birds, frogs, insects,

00:13:44.366 --> 00:13:47.725 align:middle line:84%
and the screech of monkeys deep
inside this fecund landscape.

00:13:47.725 --> 00:14:02.320 align:middle line:90%


00:14:02.320 --> 00:14:05.890 align:middle line:84%
About 10 minutes in, we cross
over rickety log bridges

00:14:05.890 --> 00:14:09.770 align:middle line:84%
strapped together
over a little creek.

00:14:09.770 --> 00:14:12.110 align:middle line:84%
A light rain falls, that
evaporates on our skin

00:14:12.110 --> 00:14:16.090 align:middle line:90%
as soon as it hits.

00:14:16.090 --> 00:14:18.610 align:middle line:84%
I guess this is why they
call it the rain-forest,

00:14:18.610 --> 00:14:21.470 align:middle line:84%
I joked to my new
friend, Vance Gellert,

00:14:21.470 --> 00:14:23.950 align:middle line:84%
as I help him lug his photo
bags through the lungs

00:14:23.950 --> 00:14:26.780 align:middle line:90%
of the earth, the Amazon.

00:14:26.780 --> 00:14:28.316 align:middle line:90%
I'm in the jungle at last.

00:14:28.316 --> 00:14:32.990 align:middle line:90%


00:14:32.990 --> 00:14:34.710 align:middle line:90%
Vance is a photographer.

00:14:34.710 --> 00:14:38.770 align:middle line:84%
He studied pharmacology
at university in the '60s.

00:14:38.770 --> 00:14:42.170 align:middle line:84%
He's been coming to the Amazon
off and on for three years now,

00:14:42.170 --> 00:14:44.720 align:middle line:84%
photographing curanderos
and the native culture

00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:50.150 align:middle line:84%
here for a book and
exhibition he's working on.

00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:53.340 align:middle line:84%
I've also roped in John
Bowman to our media cell.

00:14:53.340 --> 00:14:56.210 align:middle line:84%
A straight talking, bearded
dude from Vancouver,

00:14:56.210 --> 00:14:58.930 align:middle line:90%
who's wise beyond his 23 years.

00:14:58.930 --> 00:15:01.830 align:middle line:84%
And you turned up back at my
hostel, armed to the teeth

00:15:01.830 --> 00:15:05.490 align:middle line:84%
with broadcast quality audio
recording gear to tape shamans.

00:15:05.490 --> 00:15:13.700 align:middle line:90%


00:15:13.700 --> 00:15:17.900 align:middle line:84%
Soon we arrive at the ceremonial
maloca, a kilometer or so

00:15:17.900 --> 00:15:21.590 align:middle line:90%
past the last village.

00:15:21.590 --> 00:15:25.000 align:middle line:84%
It's a simple wall-less
hut about 20 feet long,

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:27.690 align:middle line:84%
with a thatched roof
and wooden floorboards,

00:15:27.690 --> 00:15:30.405 align:middle line:84%
surrounded by a forest of
eight foot tall plants.

00:15:30.405 --> 00:15:33.370 align:middle line:90%


00:15:33.370 --> 00:15:37.500 align:middle line:10%
100 meters distant, giant
palm trees tower about,

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:40.660 align:middle line:10%
closing off the outside world.

00:15:40.660 --> 00:15:43.870 align:middle line:84%
It looks like an alien
vista, but tonight it

00:15:43.870 --> 00:15:45.608 align:middle line:90%
will be our home and sanctuary.

00:15:45.608 --> 00:15:51.570 align:middle line:90%


00:15:51.570 --> 00:15:55.380 align:middle line:10%
We're drinking with Percy
Garcia, an indigenous curandero

00:15:55.380 --> 00:15:59.570 align:middle line:10%
in his early 30s, with shining
skin, short black hair,

00:15:59.570 --> 00:16:02.970 align:middle line:10%
and the stocky build
of native Peruvians.

00:16:02.970 --> 00:16:04.780 align:middle line:84%
He's been trained
since he was a boy

00:16:04.780 --> 00:16:07.297 align:middle line:84%
in the world of the spirits,
and of the great plant

00:16:07.297 --> 00:16:08.130 align:middle line:90%
medicine, ayahuasca.

00:16:08.130 --> 00:16:11.330 align:middle line:90%


00:16:11.330 --> 00:16:16.180 align:middle line:84%
Percy lights mapacho cigarettes
to chase away bad spirits.

00:16:16.180 --> 00:16:19.980 align:middle line:10%
They're filled with raw jungle
tobacco, Nicotiana rustica,

00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:21.110 align:middle line:10%
with 18% nicotine.

00:16:21.110 --> 00:16:27.140 align:middle line:90%


00:16:27.140 --> 00:16:29.130 align:middle line:10%
It's getting towards
early evening.

00:16:29.130 --> 00:16:31.680 align:middle line:10%
And after we get settled,
Percy takes us down

00:16:31.680 --> 00:16:35.105 align:middle line:10%
to the river 100 meters away,
to bath us in flower essences.

00:16:35.105 --> 00:16:40.990 align:middle line:90%


00:16:40.990 --> 00:16:43.470 align:middle line:84%
Percy bathes our heads,
and blows smoke down

00:16:43.470 --> 00:16:47.580 align:middle line:84%
the back of our necks and
over our crown chakras.

00:16:47.580 --> 00:16:51.100 align:middle line:84%
It feels like the hot breath
of nightclub smoke machines,

00:16:51.100 --> 00:16:53.600 align:middle line:84%
but it's a very
intimate situation.

00:16:53.600 --> 00:16:56.710 align:middle line:84%
And as I look up at Percy's
always beaming face,

00:16:56.710 --> 00:16:59.530 align:middle line:84%
with his shiny skin
and dark black eyes,

00:16:59.530 --> 00:17:01.330 align:middle line:84%
he still looks like
he's just stepped out

00:17:01.330 --> 00:17:03.860 align:middle line:90%
of the World Cup football tour.

00:17:03.860 --> 00:17:07.079 align:middle line:84%
But he is also a
curandero, a healer.

00:17:07.079 --> 00:17:10.339 align:middle line:84%
And I start to realize
the responsibility he has,

00:17:10.339 --> 00:17:12.750 align:middle line:84%
that tonight he will lead
us through the subtle zones

00:17:12.750 --> 00:17:13.406 align:middle line:90%
of the spirit.

00:17:13.406 --> 00:17:16.569 align:middle line:90%


00:17:16.569 --> 00:17:20.680 align:middle line:84%
One by one, we are called
up and leave the river.

00:17:20.680 --> 00:17:23.030 align:middle line:84%
Baptized into the
ways of the jungle

00:17:23.030 --> 00:17:24.420 align:middle line:90%
by the fading dusk light.

00:17:24.420 --> 00:17:39.310 align:middle line:90%


00:17:39.310 --> 00:17:42.690 align:middle line:84%
As we wander back to the
maloca in the crisp night air,

00:17:42.690 --> 00:17:46.540 align:middle line:84%
its thatched frame is
lit by dozens of candles.

00:17:46.540 --> 00:17:49.660 align:middle line:84%
It looks like a fairy
house in the jungle.

00:17:49.660 --> 00:17:52.140 align:middle line:84%
We take our spots on
the floor and shake out

00:17:52.140 --> 00:17:53.820 align:middle line:90%
our sleeping bags.

00:17:53.820 --> 00:17:56.810 align:middle line:84%
And Percy's assistant,
Carlos, explains to us

00:17:56.810 --> 00:17:59.880 align:middle line:84%
that Percy comes from a
long line of curanderos,

00:17:59.880 --> 00:18:03.740 align:middle line:84%
in a tradition where you
were born into the role.

00:18:03.740 --> 00:18:07.659 align:middle line:84%
Percy was prepared by his
grandfather, a Banco shaman,

00:18:07.659 --> 00:18:09.200 align:middle line:84%
who started grooming
him in the plant

00:18:09.200 --> 00:18:12.010 align:middle line:90%
medicines that the age of 10.

00:18:12.010 --> 00:18:14.520 align:middle line:84%
He started drinking
ayahuasca at 14,

00:18:14.520 --> 00:18:17.750 align:middle line:84%
and learning from other teachers
after his grandfather died,

00:18:17.750 --> 00:18:22.210 align:middle line:84%
rising up to become
the village healer.

00:18:22.210 --> 00:18:26.100 align:middle line:84%
You don't choose to become
a curandera, Percy says.

00:18:26.100 --> 00:18:28.040 align:middle line:84%
And the few that do
will enter the science

00:18:28.040 --> 00:18:29.456 align:middle line:84%
because they are
called by spirit.

00:18:29.456 --> 00:18:36.570 align:middle line:90%


00:18:36.570 --> 00:18:40.060 align:middle line:84%
The night is alive with the
sounds of insects and animals,

00:18:40.060 --> 00:18:43.280 align:middle line:84%
like a constant
hum of electricity.

00:18:43.280 --> 00:18:46.550 align:middle line:84%
Percy's ceremonial garb
is a curious mishmash

00:18:46.550 --> 00:18:48.110 align:middle line:84%
of Western clothes
and indigenous

00:18:48.110 --> 00:18:52.410 align:middle line:84%
bling that visually sums up the
changing nature of shamanism.

00:18:52.410 --> 00:18:56.390 align:middle line:84%
A tiger t-shirt, silk
spotted pants and sneakers,

00:18:56.390 --> 00:18:59.680 align:middle line:84%
a feathered parrot hat with
blue, red, and yellow feathers

00:18:59.680 --> 00:19:03.635 align:middle line:84%
offset by Christian rosary
beads and a chakapa leaf fan

00:19:03.635 --> 00:19:04.625 align:middle line:90%
in one hand.

00:19:04.625 --> 00:19:07.600 align:middle line:90%


00:19:07.600 --> 00:19:11.270 align:middle line:10%
He sits behind a makeshift
alter, a wooden box covered

00:19:11.270 --> 00:19:14.940 align:middle line:10%
with an intricate, geometrically
patterned cloth like those

00:19:14.940 --> 00:19:17.000 align:middle line:10%
the Shipibo women were selling.

00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:19.570 align:middle line:84%
The visual trip reports of
the ayahuascan head-space.

00:19:19.570 --> 00:19:28.220 align:middle line:90%


00:19:28.220 --> 00:19:31.190 align:middle line:10%
The altar is covered
with ceremonial objects,

00:19:31.190 --> 00:19:35.280 align:middle line:10%
little rainbow bead dolls,
wooden cups, and about 100

00:19:35.280 --> 00:19:38.060 align:middle line:10%
giant mapacho cigarettes.

00:19:38.060 --> 00:19:40.740 align:middle line:10%
And last but not
least, in plastic,

00:19:40.740 --> 00:19:43.110 align:middle line:10%
two liter San Luis
water bottles,

00:19:43.110 --> 00:19:45.980 align:middle line:10%
a thick, dark brown liquid.

00:19:45.980 --> 00:19:46.850 align:middle line:90%
Ayahuasca.

00:19:46.850 --> 00:19:47.820 align:middle line:90%
The vine of souls.

00:19:47.820 --> 00:19:53.480 align:middle line:90%


00:19:53.480 --> 00:19:57.890 align:middle line:84%
Ayahuasca is Quechua for
vine of the dead souls.

00:19:57.890 --> 00:20:00.380 align:middle line:84%
But at the same
time, as a healer,

00:20:00.380 --> 00:20:02.270 align:middle line:90%
we don't call them dead spirits.

00:20:02.270 --> 00:20:04.470 align:middle line:84%
We call them allies,
Percy explains

00:20:04.470 --> 00:20:07.014 align:middle line:90%
through his interpreter.

00:20:07.014 --> 00:20:09.730 align:middle line:84%
Ayahuasca is medicine,
he continues.

00:20:09.730 --> 00:20:13.570 align:middle line:84%
It is strength, intelligence,
wisdom, and healing.

00:20:13.570 --> 00:20:17.710 align:middle line:84%
In this way, everything is
in accord with tradition.

00:20:17.710 --> 00:20:21.500 align:middle line:84%
While nature represents
what life is, ayahuasca is

00:20:21.500 --> 00:20:23.330 align:middle line:90%
the mother of us all, he says.

00:20:23.330 --> 00:20:31.140 align:middle line:90%


00:20:31.140 --> 00:20:33.230 align:middle line:10%
>>You may consider
myself a teacher.

00:20:33.230 --> 00:20:42.380 align:middle line:90%


00:20:42.380 --> 00:20:45.440 align:middle line:10%
But as a matter of fact, I
consider myself another student

00:20:45.440 --> 00:20:46.460 align:middle line:10%
from mother nature.

00:20:46.460 --> 00:20:56.032 align:middle line:90%


00:20:56.032 --> 00:20:57.240 align:middle line:90%
The doctors are the teachers.

00:20:57.240 --> 00:21:01.525 align:middle line:90%


00:21:01.525 --> 00:21:07.070 align:middle line:84%
Those who guide me to
perform the healing.

00:21:07.070 --> 00:21:14.690 align:middle line:90%


00:21:14.690 --> 00:21:17.690 align:middle line:10%
>>Percy doles out the
ayahuasca by torchlight.

00:21:17.690 --> 00:21:21.210 align:middle line:84%
And we drink, one by one,
going up to the altar

00:21:21.210 --> 00:21:25.450 align:middle line:84%
and taking the medicine
in little wooden bowls.

00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:27.820 align:middle line:84%
The brew is dark
and phlegm-life.

00:21:27.820 --> 00:21:30.280 align:middle line:84%
And like all medicines,
it tastes foul.

00:21:30.280 --> 00:21:33.370 align:middle line:84%
An earthy flavor that
hits the quick of you,

00:21:33.370 --> 00:21:34.900 align:middle line:90%
and threatens to come up again.

00:21:34.900 --> 00:21:43.190 align:middle line:90%


00:21:43.190 --> 00:21:45.700 align:middle line:84%
People burp and rinse
their mouths around me,

00:21:45.700 --> 00:21:47.730 align:middle line:84%
as I clench down
the bitter flavor

00:21:47.730 --> 00:21:50.890 align:middle line:84%
and breathe through it,
feeling its warmth sink down

00:21:50.890 --> 00:21:51.590 align:middle line:90%
into my belly.

00:21:51.590 --> 00:22:00.250 align:middle line:90%


00:22:00.250 --> 00:22:01.896 align:middle line:90%
The blood of the vine.

00:22:01.896 --> 00:22:04.770 align:middle line:84%
Plant medicine to
make you strong.

00:22:04.770 --> 00:22:05.860 align:middle line:90%
Keep it down.

00:22:05.860 --> 00:22:06.950 align:middle line:90%
Let it pour into you.

00:22:06.950 --> 00:22:09.470 align:middle line:84%
Fill you with
plant-human interface.

00:22:09.470 --> 00:22:12.090 align:middle line:90%


00:22:12.090 --> 00:22:15.400 align:middle line:84%
Outside, the sounds
of the jungle deepen.

00:22:15.400 --> 00:22:18.420 align:middle line:84%
Monkeys screech and
parrots call to each other,

00:22:18.420 --> 00:22:20.990 align:middle line:84%
and the ubiquitous sound
of insects, as always,

00:22:20.990 --> 00:22:22.930 align:middle line:90%
is switched on.

00:22:22.930 --> 00:22:24.260 align:middle line:90%
Now, so are we.

00:22:24.260 --> 00:22:27.980 align:middle line:90%


00:22:27.980 --> 00:22:31.510 align:middle line:84%
As the minutes go by, we
collapse into our mattresses,

00:22:31.510 --> 00:22:34.070 align:middle line:84%
and the sound of
vomiting fills the air.

00:22:34.070 --> 00:22:36.760 align:middle line:90%
La purga, the natives call it.

00:22:36.760 --> 00:22:39.630 align:middle line:90%
The purge.

00:22:39.630 --> 00:22:43.020 align:middle line:84%
Racking heaves of spew
usher forth from gringos

00:22:43.020 --> 00:22:46.920 align:middle line:84%
all around me, as the ayahuasca
reads their energetic bodies,

00:22:46.920 --> 00:22:50.460 align:middle line:84%
finds the sickness within,
and brings it up and out,

00:22:50.460 --> 00:22:54.080 align:middle line:90%
sometimes from both ends.

00:22:54.080 --> 00:22:56.710 align:middle line:84%
When you are surrounded by
a group of fellow ayahuasca

00:22:56.710 --> 00:23:01.610 align:middle line:84%
drinkers in ceremony, their
energies overlap your own.

00:23:01.610 --> 00:23:04.550 align:middle line:84%
And as the ayahuasca
heightens your senses,

00:23:04.550 --> 00:23:07.500 align:middle line:84%
the sound of gringos drinking,
and vomiting, and rolling

00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:10.430 align:middle line:90%
around, can be overwhelming.

00:23:10.430 --> 00:23:15.400 align:middle line:84%
Every noise, every word, every
look and breath sinks into you

00:23:15.400 --> 00:23:17.430 align:middle line:90%
until you can't look at them.

00:23:17.430 --> 00:23:20.100 align:middle line:84%
You need to reel in
your own psychic energy

00:23:20.100 --> 00:23:22.410 align:middle line:84%
and contain it
within yourself, not

00:23:22.410 --> 00:23:24.570 align:middle line:84%
contaminate it with
other's energies,

00:23:24.570 --> 00:23:25.840 align:middle line:90%
no matter how good natured.

00:23:25.840 --> 00:23:28.792 align:middle line:90%


00:23:28.792 --> 00:23:32.236 align:middle line:90%
[JUNGLE NOISES]

00:23:32.236 --> 00:23:49.960 align:middle line:90%


00:23:49.960 --> 00:23:53.850 align:middle line:84%
I can feel myself
gently slipping away

00:23:53.850 --> 00:23:57.560 align:middle line:84%
into a light trance as
the candles are blown out.

00:23:57.560 --> 00:24:00.160 align:middle line:84%
And my last thought is
that we have gone back

00:24:00.160 --> 00:24:04.370 align:middle line:84%
to the jungle, back to
the great green womb.

00:24:04.370 --> 00:24:10.090 align:middle line:84%
We've returned full circle
from whence we came.

00:24:10.090 --> 00:24:13.340 align:middle line:84%
The ayahuasca starts
to come on slow,

00:24:13.340 --> 00:24:16.420 align:middle line:90%
snaking in and out like a lover.

00:24:16.420 --> 00:24:18.080 align:middle line:90%
Tantalizing me.

00:24:18.080 --> 00:24:21.630 align:middle line:84%
The spirit in the plant
is playing hard to get.

00:24:21.630 --> 00:24:25.820 align:middle line:84%
Or more likely, she's
finding me hard to get.

00:24:25.820 --> 00:24:29.630 align:middle line:84%
She's interfacing,
overlapping energy fields,

00:24:29.630 --> 00:24:31.935 align:middle line:84%
as her jungle medicine
comes on strong.

00:24:31.935 --> 00:24:36.880 align:middle line:90%


00:24:36.880 --> 00:24:41.560 align:middle line:84%
There's a flash of vibrant green
as something starts to happen,

00:24:41.560 --> 00:24:44.490 align:middle line:84%
as I fall into
this target window

00:24:44.490 --> 00:24:47.230 align:middle line:84%
of curious,
circuitry-like patterns.

00:24:47.230 --> 00:24:51.530 align:middle line:84%
Lines of energy that are
called ayahuasca rivers.

00:24:51.530 --> 00:24:55.310 align:middle line:84%
Locks deep inside me, that
I never knew were there,

00:24:55.310 --> 00:24:57.230 align:middle line:90%
are tumbling open.

00:24:57.230 --> 00:25:00.920 align:middle line:84%
And I'm spilling into
the spaces they reveal.

00:25:00.920 --> 00:25:03.040 align:middle line:90%
Wrapped inside the mother.

00:25:03.040 --> 00:25:07.170 align:middle line:84%
She who nurtures and destroys
in her endless embrace.

00:25:07.170 --> 00:25:10.840 align:middle line:84%
All those I love flash
before my mind's eye

00:25:10.840 --> 00:25:13.225 align:middle line:84%
in a slow-motion,
emotional retrospective.

00:25:13.225 --> 00:25:16.700 align:middle line:90%


00:25:16.700 --> 00:25:20.430 align:middle line:84%
I feel like I'm being
unwound and examined.

00:25:20.430 --> 00:25:22.540 align:middle line:84%
But I'm not sure
if this is for me,

00:25:22.540 --> 00:25:24.630 align:middle line:84%
or for the spirit
of ayahuasca, to get

00:25:24.630 --> 00:25:28.460 align:middle line:84%
a quick vibrational
diagnostic on the patient.

00:25:28.460 --> 00:25:31.350 align:middle line:84%
I'm an open book
to her gaze, as I

00:25:31.350 --> 00:25:34.640 align:middle line:84%
circumnavigate these hot
spaces, and heal the way I

00:25:34.640 --> 00:25:37.870 align:middle line:90%
feel to each of my loved ones.

00:25:37.870 --> 00:25:41.040 align:middle line:84%
And then, Madre
Ayahuasca shows me

00:25:41.040 --> 00:25:42.930 align:middle line:84%
bits of myself
that lay forgotten

00:25:42.930 --> 00:25:47.230 align:middle line:84%
or unused, like rooms to a
house I've lived in all my life,

00:25:47.230 --> 00:25:48.150 align:middle line:90%
but never entered.

00:25:48.150 --> 00:25:52.250 align:middle line:90%


00:25:52.250 --> 00:25:55.646 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE CHANTING]

00:25:55.646 --> 00:26:16.690 align:middle line:90%


00:26:16.690 --> 00:26:19.960 align:middle line:84%
>>Percy cuts through the
night with his haunting voice,

00:26:19.960 --> 00:26:22.135 align:middle line:84%
singing a beautiful
rhythmic chant

00:26:22.135 --> 00:26:26.130 align:middle line:84%
that carries healing energy
on the current of its time.

00:26:26.130 --> 00:26:29.760 align:middle line:84%
He sings, sweet and
gentle as mother's milk,

00:26:29.760 --> 00:26:32.800 align:middle line:84%
like a nursery song sung
to babies while suckling

00:26:32.800 --> 00:26:34.930 align:middle line:90%
at their mother's breast.

00:26:34.930 --> 00:26:38.550 align:middle line:84%
And then he comes around, and
he blows mapacho smoke over us,

00:26:38.550 --> 00:26:43.880 align:middle line:84%
smudging us, shaking loose
any negative into the ether.

00:26:43.880 --> 00:26:47.440 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE CHANTING]

00:26:47.440 --> 00:26:54.220 align:middle line:90%


00:26:54.220 --> 00:26:56.330 align:middle line:84%
>>>>[SIGHS] I feel
like the ayahuasca

00:26:56.330 --> 00:26:59.370 align:middle line:84%
is getting to know me
from the inside out.

00:26:59.370 --> 00:27:01.395 align:middle line:90%
But I'm trying to control her.

00:27:01.395 --> 00:27:04.375 align:middle line:84%
I'm static and blocking her
ability to come through.

00:27:04.375 --> 00:27:07.470 align:middle line:90%


00:27:07.470 --> 00:27:10.040 align:middle line:84%
The circuitry
patters come and go

00:27:10.040 --> 00:27:12.950 align:middle line:84%
as I struggle with
the vine in me now.

00:27:12.950 --> 00:27:15.850 align:middle line:84%
Still holding on and
breathing through the cramps

00:27:15.850 --> 00:27:17.100 align:middle line:90%
in my stomach.

00:27:17.100 --> 00:27:18.975 align:middle line:84%
And the pressure
building in my bowels.

00:27:18.975 --> 00:27:33.200 align:middle line:90%


00:27:33.200 --> 00:27:36.220 align:middle line:84%
It's only when all the others
seem to have fallen asleep,

00:27:36.220 --> 00:27:38.250 align:middle line:84%
in the wee hours
of the night, can I

00:27:38.250 --> 00:27:40.760 align:middle line:84%
bring myself to get
up and creep out

00:27:40.760 --> 00:27:43.870 align:middle line:90%
deep into the jungle to purge.

00:27:43.870 --> 00:27:47.230 align:middle line:90%
[VOMITING SOUNDS]

00:27:47.230 --> 00:27:49.640 align:middle line:90%


00:27:49.640 --> 00:27:53.180 align:middle line:84%
As I look up from my vomit,
I can see water particles

00:27:53.180 --> 00:27:57.140 align:middle line:84%
hanging in the air, like
a swarm of liquid bees.

00:27:57.140 --> 00:27:59.820 align:middle line:90%
Tiny glowing beads of moisture.

00:27:59.820 --> 00:28:02.830 align:middle line:90%
Jungle juice.

00:28:02.830 --> 00:28:05.160 align:middle line:84%
Glistening amongst
the beads are glowing

00:28:05.160 --> 00:28:08.240 align:middle line:84%
mitochondrial-like
amoebas, illuminated

00:28:08.240 --> 00:28:11.256 align:middle line:90%
by the light from my head torch.

00:28:11.256 --> 00:28:15.070 align:middle line:84%
I can't for the life of me
figure out what they are.

00:28:15.070 --> 00:28:18.450 align:middle line:84%
They hang there
preternaturally in the light.

00:28:18.450 --> 00:28:21.970 align:middle line:84%
And as I reach out my hand
and wave it in the air,

00:28:21.970 --> 00:28:25.990 align:middle line:84%
the beads curl and swirl in
an equal and opposite reaction

00:28:25.990 --> 00:28:28.050 align:middle line:90%
to my motion.

00:28:28.050 --> 00:28:30.450 align:middle line:90%
And then it hits me.

00:28:30.450 --> 00:28:34.220 align:middle line:84%
This is the breath of the
mother, visible, and exhaling

00:28:34.220 --> 00:28:34.820 align:middle line:90%
all around.

00:28:34.820 --> 00:28:38.580 align:middle line:90%


00:28:38.580 --> 00:28:40.610 align:middle line:90%
Ah, God.

00:28:40.610 --> 00:28:44.930 align:middle line:84%
The ayahuasca is hitting me
now, changing my perceptions,

00:28:44.930 --> 00:28:49.200 align:middle line:84%
deepening my emotional
connection to the web of life.

00:28:49.200 --> 00:28:53.770 align:middle line:84%
It's like there's an invisible
thread, and if you pull on it,

00:28:53.770 --> 00:28:56.750 align:middle line:84%
the whole picture will unravel,
revealing the true pattern

00:28:56.750 --> 00:28:57.250 align:middle line:90%
underneath.

00:28:57.250 --> 00:29:02.220 align:middle line:90%


00:29:02.220 --> 00:29:05.750 align:middle line:84%
I feel I'm intimately connected
to everything around me

00:29:05.750 --> 00:29:10.330 align:middle line:84%
by my vibrational wave front
to that great atomic sea where

00:29:10.330 --> 00:29:13.040 align:middle line:90%
we are all one.

00:29:13.040 --> 00:29:15.510 align:middle line:84%
Safe in the great
green womb, I'm

00:29:15.510 --> 00:29:18.830 align:middle line:84%
remembering what this
connection means, and who

00:29:18.830 --> 00:29:20.880 align:middle line:90%
and what we really are.

00:29:20.880 --> 00:29:23.800 align:middle line:84%
And it is then that I
realize, as the vine spreads

00:29:23.800 --> 00:29:26.610 align:middle line:84%
its tendrils around
the globe, people

00:29:26.610 --> 00:29:29.160 align:middle line:84%
have to stop thinking
they are in control,

00:29:29.160 --> 00:29:31.460 align:middle line:90%
and sit back and have faith.

00:29:31.460 --> 00:29:35.926 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe, I've got
the jungle fever.

00:29:35.926 --> 00:29:39.314 align:middle line:90%
[JUNGLE NOISES]

00:29:39.314 --> 00:29:47.080 align:middle line:90%


00:29:47.080 --> 00:29:49.420 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE SINGING]

00:29:49.420 --> 00:30:15.770 align:middle line:90%


00:30:15.770 --> 00:30:20.280 align:middle line:84%
Bowman, Vance, and I walk
under the blue Peruvian sky

00:30:20.280 --> 00:30:22.510 align:middle line:84%
and marvel at the
giant cumulonimbus

00:30:22.510 --> 00:30:25.480 align:middle line:90%
clouds billowing overhead.

00:30:25.480 --> 00:30:28.380 align:middle line:84%
We take some panoramic
shots with our cameras,

00:30:28.380 --> 00:30:31.018 align:middle line:84%
capturing everything but
the spirit of this place.

00:30:31.018 --> 00:30:35.360 align:middle line:90%


00:30:35.360 --> 00:30:38.110 align:middle line:84%
After a few kilometers,
we reach a sign which

00:30:38.110 --> 00:30:41.710 align:middle line:90%
reads, "Espiritu de Anaconda."

00:30:41.710 --> 00:30:43.845 align:middle line:84%
Walking over wooden
bridges, we pass

00:30:43.845 --> 00:30:46.570 align:middle line:84%
the lush, cultured
rain-forest and enter

00:30:46.570 --> 00:30:49.960 align:middle line:84%
into a sprawling,
multi-unit complex designed

00:30:49.960 --> 00:30:53.640 align:middle line:90%
to cater to Western standards.

00:30:53.640 --> 00:30:57.010 align:middle line:10%
The central maloca is
about 30 feet in diameter,

00:30:57.010 --> 00:31:00.230 align:middle line:10%
with a conical roof that
reaches almost as high again,

00:31:00.230 --> 00:31:03.520 align:middle line:10%
and houses over
two dozen people.

00:31:03.520 --> 00:31:06.890 align:middle line:84%
It's booked full tonight with
conference attendees wanting

00:31:06.890 --> 00:31:08.310 align:middle line:90%
to drink ayahuasca.

00:31:08.310 --> 00:31:11.694 align:middle line:84%
In this Amazonian cathedral,
fully mosquito-proofed,

00:31:11.694 --> 00:31:13.235 align:middle line:84%
leave your shoes at
the door, please.

00:31:13.235 --> 00:31:15.980 align:middle line:90%


00:31:15.980 --> 00:31:19.720 align:middle line:84%
Add a dozen smaller malocas,
guest houses, the dining room

00:31:19.720 --> 00:31:22.619 align:middle line:84%
and toilets with
porcelain bowls and doors,

00:31:22.619 --> 00:31:24.910 align:middle line:84%
and this starts to feel like
the Club Med of ayahuasca.

00:31:24.910 --> 00:31:28.970 align:middle line:90%


00:31:28.970 --> 00:31:31.660 align:middle line:10%
Guillermo Arabella is
one of the most famous

00:31:31.660 --> 00:31:34.910 align:middle line:10%
Peruvian curanderos, having
starred French filmmaker,

00:31:34.910 --> 00:31:38.940 align:middle line:10%
Jan Kounen's feature length
psychedelic spaghetti Western,

00:31:38.940 --> 00:31:42.230 align:middle line:10%
"Renegade," which communicated
the visual hallucinations

00:31:42.230 --> 00:31:46.440 align:middle line:10%
and experience the spirit
of the vine can bring.

00:31:46.440 --> 00:31:48.890 align:middle line:10%
He moved here from
his native Pucallpa,

00:31:48.890 --> 00:31:51.240 align:middle line:10%
and built the center
only two years ago,

00:31:51.240 --> 00:31:56.490 align:middle line:10%
after money from the movie
gave him the capital to expand.

00:31:56.490 --> 00:31:58.710 align:middle line:84%
I saw him at the
shaman conference,

00:31:58.710 --> 00:32:00.410 align:middle line:84%
it was a bit like
seeing Tom Cruise

00:32:00.410 --> 00:32:03.540 align:middle line:84%
in the flesh for the first
time, and realizing he's shorter

00:32:03.540 --> 00:32:06.960 align:middle line:90%
than he seems on the screen.

00:32:06.960 --> 00:32:10.370 align:middle line:84%
At five foot two, and stripped
of any robes or ceremony

00:32:10.370 --> 00:32:14.730 align:middle line:84%
trappings, Guillermo is a simple
man, with his cropped gray hair

00:32:14.730 --> 00:32:17.460 align:middle line:84%
speckled with white,
and a tight lipped smile

00:32:17.460 --> 00:32:21.430 align:middle line:90%
across his broad Peruvian face.

00:32:21.430 --> 00:32:24.140 align:middle line:84%
In a wall-less hut
behind the main maloca,

00:32:24.140 --> 00:32:26.090 align:middle line:84%
one of Guillermo's
helpers is boiling up

00:32:26.090 --> 00:32:28.720 align:middle line:84%
crushed ayahuasca
vine and other plants

00:32:28.720 --> 00:32:32.570 align:middle line:84%
in a giant
soot-blackened cauldron.

00:32:32.570 --> 00:32:35.740 align:middle line:84%
As the flames lick up
and spray into the air,

00:32:35.740 --> 00:32:39.440 align:middle line:84%
it resembles a witches pot, with
the attendant in his shorts,

00:32:39.440 --> 00:32:41.980 align:middle line:90%
t-shirt and baseball cap.

00:32:41.980 --> 00:32:47.080 align:middle line:84%
A plume of thick, gray smoke
billows out, stinging my eyes.

00:32:47.080 --> 00:32:50.740 align:middle line:84%
When they clear, I can see the
jungle medicine, ayahuasca,

00:32:50.740 --> 00:32:53.490 align:middle line:84%
brewing, bubbling,
writhing with life.

00:32:53.490 --> 00:32:57.540 align:middle line:90%


00:32:57.540 --> 00:32:59.720 align:middle line:84%
And around the thick
brown vine are green,

00:32:59.720 --> 00:33:03.820 align:middle line:84%
admixture leaves that
contain the active DMT.

00:33:03.820 --> 00:33:07.260 align:middle line:84%
I get a whiff of the brew,
and it makes me want to vomit.

00:33:07.260 --> 00:33:10.220 align:middle line:84%
The surged memory of
ayahuasca washes up,

00:33:10.220 --> 00:33:13.370 align:middle line:84%
the taste of my last experience
catching in my throat.

00:33:13.370 --> 00:33:15.200 align:middle line:90%
I struggle to force it down.

00:33:15.200 --> 00:33:21.840 align:middle line:90%


00:33:21.840 --> 00:33:25.000 align:middle line:84%
They say it takes a few years
for the ayahuasca drinker's

00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:28.680 align:middle line:84%
body to get used to the brew
and properly acclimatize.

00:33:28.680 --> 00:33:30.030 align:middle line:90%
But the soul?

00:33:30.030 --> 00:33:31.480 align:middle line:90%
That takes longer.

00:33:31.480 --> 00:33:32.230 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes forever.

00:33:32.230 --> 00:33:38.032 align:middle line:90%


00:33:38.032 --> 00:33:39.860 align:middle line:90%
Ayahuasca is not a drug.

00:33:39.860 --> 00:33:41.480 align:middle line:90%
Not in the Western sense.

00:33:41.480 --> 00:33:44.940 align:middle line:84%
It cannot be abused like
recreational chemicals

00:33:44.940 --> 00:33:48.050 align:middle line:84%
because the taste and
experience is so demanding,

00:33:48.050 --> 00:33:52.480 align:middle line:84%
and the hallucinogenic effect
is never the same twice.

00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:56.310 align:middle line:84%
Rather, it develops a
relationship with a drinker,

00:33:56.310 --> 00:33:59.260 align:middle line:84%
sometimes healing the body,
other times illuminating

00:33:59.260 --> 00:33:59.940 align:middle line:90%
the mind.

00:33:59.940 --> 00:34:05.110 align:middle line:84%
Or deeper still, taking the
soul on journeys beyond.

00:34:05.110 --> 00:34:07.708 align:middle line:84%
But it would do none of this
without the participant putting

00:34:07.708 --> 00:34:09.130 align:middle line:90%
effort in.

00:34:09.130 --> 00:34:13.420 align:middle line:84%
It's not just, pop the red
pill and escape the matrix.

00:34:13.420 --> 00:34:16.929 align:middle line:84%
Serious students have to
give up their Western ways

00:34:16.929 --> 00:34:21.190 align:middle line:84%
and embrace a rigorous diet, low
in foods containing tyramine,

00:34:21.190 --> 00:34:23.909 align:middle line:84%
a chemical which can react
badly with the MAO inhibiting

00:34:23.909 --> 00:34:26.370 align:middle line:90%
properties of the vine.

00:34:26.370 --> 00:34:31.909 align:middle line:84%
No red meat, pork, salt, sugar,
fat, caffeine, acetic food,

00:34:31.909 --> 00:34:35.980 align:middle line:84%
alcohol, or sex, all of which
affect the body's sensitivity

00:34:35.980 --> 00:34:37.430 align:middle line:90%
to ayahuasca.

00:34:37.430 --> 00:34:40.940 align:middle line:84%
But tell that to a bunch of
Western thrill seekers looking

00:34:40.940 --> 00:34:42.951 align:middle line:90%
for some jungle kicks.

00:34:42.951 --> 00:34:46.903 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE CHANTING]

00:34:46.903 --> 00:36:31.520 align:middle line:90%


00:36:31.520 --> 00:36:33.360 align:middle line:90%
>>Spoken like a true Jedi.

00:36:33.360 --> 00:36:39.036 align:middle line:90%


00:36:39.036 --> 00:36:42.070 align:middle line:90%
At sunset, we drink.

00:36:42.070 --> 00:36:44.400 align:middle line:84%
And I learned that when you
spend the night in pitch

00:36:44.400 --> 00:36:46.350 align:middle line:84%
darkness with a
large group of people

00:36:46.350 --> 00:36:51.725 align:middle line:84%
and take ayahuasca,
purging, sweating, dying

00:36:51.725 --> 00:36:54.580 align:middle line:84%
and re-birthing
together, you get

00:36:54.580 --> 00:36:57.750 align:middle line:90%
to know each other pretty well.

00:36:57.750 --> 00:36:59.660 align:middle line:84%
You might not
remember their name,

00:36:59.660 --> 00:37:03.570 align:middle line:84%
but afterwards, you remember
their face and the sound

00:37:03.570 --> 00:37:04.970 align:middle line:90%
of their suffering.

00:37:04.970 --> 00:37:06.650 align:middle line:90%
And they yours.

00:37:06.650 --> 00:37:10.690 align:middle line:84%
And there is a special
bond between you.

00:37:10.690 --> 00:37:14.081 align:middle line:84%
The candle goes out
and it's pitch black.

00:37:14.081 --> 00:37:18.330 align:middle line:84%
A heavy stillness hangs in
the air like a burlap curtain.

00:37:18.330 --> 00:37:19.390 align:middle line:90%
Maybe that's the spirits.

00:37:19.390 --> 00:37:22.840 align:middle line:90%


00:37:22.840 --> 00:37:26.050 align:middle line:84%
Everyone is quiet,
moving around slightly,

00:37:26.050 --> 00:37:28.950 align:middle line:84%
the silence of the
moment punctuated

00:37:28.950 --> 00:37:32.750 align:middle line:84%
by the inevitable Promethean
heave of another drinker

00:37:32.750 --> 00:37:33.250 align:middle line:90%
vomiting.

00:37:33.250 --> 00:37:36.020 align:middle line:90%


00:37:36.020 --> 00:37:42.570 align:middle line:84%
And as they vomit, up come
all their hurts, their pain,

00:37:42.570 --> 00:37:44.186 align:middle line:90%
their suppressions and ills.

00:37:44.186 --> 00:37:47.162 align:middle line:90%


00:37:47.162 --> 00:37:49.600 align:middle line:90%
I'm starting to come on slow.

00:37:49.600 --> 00:37:52.750 align:middle line:84%
A warm, billowing
head-space enlarging

00:37:52.750 --> 00:37:58.710 align:middle line:84%
to take in the whole maloca,
and the spirit zone phasing in.

00:37:58.710 --> 00:38:01.810 align:middle line:84%
To my left, Bowman darts
forward and crouches

00:38:01.810 --> 00:38:03.810 align:middle line:84%
by the round,
plastic bowl placed

00:38:03.810 --> 00:38:05.890 align:middle line:90%
at the end of his mattress.

00:38:05.890 --> 00:38:09.460 align:middle line:84%
Gripping it with both hands, he
makes a swift, sharp gurgling

00:38:09.460 --> 00:38:12.850 align:middle line:90%
sound, and vomits quickly.

00:38:12.850 --> 00:38:15.710 align:middle line:84%
I can see his shape and
the outline of his back

00:38:15.710 --> 00:38:18.070 align:middle line:84%
in the diffuse
moonlight that shines

00:38:18.070 --> 00:38:21.260 align:middle line:84%
through the thick mosquito
nets that surround the maloca.

00:38:21.260 --> 00:38:25.110 align:middle line:84%
Heaving over and over,
the spirit of ayahuasca

00:38:25.110 --> 00:38:28.440 align:middle line:84%
finding another dark crevice
and bringing it to the light.

00:38:28.440 --> 00:38:42.320 align:middle line:90%


00:38:42.320 --> 00:38:45.120 align:middle line:84%
There's no point or
focus in this darkness.

00:38:45.120 --> 00:38:47.500 align:middle line:90%
No sense of time progressing.

00:38:47.500 --> 00:38:51.630 align:middle line:84%
To the unprepared,
this could be hell.

00:38:51.630 --> 00:38:54.270 align:middle line:84%
Possessed by a strange
spirit, your body

00:38:54.270 --> 00:38:57.880 align:middle line:84%
wracked by wave
after wave of nausea,

00:38:57.880 --> 00:39:00.637 align:middle line:84%
vomiting up green bile
in crushing waves.

00:39:00.637 --> 00:39:03.380 align:middle line:90%


00:39:03.380 --> 00:39:07.010 align:middle line:84%
My head is awash with the
psychic weight of my own mind.

00:39:07.010 --> 00:39:10.170 align:middle line:84%
Past loves, mistakes,
issues from my life

00:39:10.170 --> 00:39:12.430 align:middle line:90%
all flash before my eyes.

00:39:12.430 --> 00:39:15.464 align:middle line:84%
But I'm not sure if my
brain is just hyperactive

00:39:15.464 --> 00:39:17.130 align:middle line:84%
or if there's something
deeper going on.

00:39:17.130 --> 00:39:20.110 align:middle line:90%


00:39:20.110 --> 00:39:23.920 align:middle line:84%
In the darkness, my mind
is up to its old tricks,

00:39:23.920 --> 00:39:27.490 align:middle line:84%
trying to imprint form
on the primal chaos.

00:39:27.490 --> 00:39:31.280 align:middle line:84%
I want to see snakes and
alligator, jaguar totem

00:39:31.280 --> 00:39:32.530 align:middle line:90%
spirits.

00:39:32.530 --> 00:39:36.220 align:middle line:84%
And I want it so much my
mind is doing its best.

00:39:36.220 --> 00:39:39.800 align:middle line:84%
Grabbing at the shadows and
seeing eyes and slithering,

00:39:39.800 --> 00:39:41.085 align:middle line:90%
obsidian dream snakes.

00:39:41.085 --> 00:39:52.110 align:middle line:90%


00:39:52.110 --> 00:39:56.920 align:middle line:84%
Guillermo's staccato
breath punctuates the dark.

00:39:56.920 --> 00:39:58.960 align:middle line:84%
Short, pitched
sounds that strike

00:39:58.960 --> 00:40:01.310 align:middle line:84%
like compressed
air darts and cut

00:40:01.310 --> 00:40:04.670 align:middle line:84%
through the heavy
atmosphere around us.

00:40:04.670 --> 00:40:08.010 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the most eclectic
sounds I've ever heard.

00:40:08.010 --> 00:40:11.860 align:middle line:84%
Distinctly sentient, with
an intelligence behind it.

00:40:11.860 --> 00:40:14.200 align:middle line:84%
But at the same
time insect-like,

00:40:14.200 --> 00:40:17.428 align:middle line:84%
alien, and just beyond the
reach of the conscious mind.

00:40:17.428 --> 00:40:20.350 align:middle line:90%


00:40:20.350 --> 00:40:24.040 align:middle line:84%
It cuts through the dark,
churning in my consciousness,

00:40:24.040 --> 00:40:27.220 align:middle line:84%
as something cracks along
the back of my skull.

00:40:27.220 --> 00:40:30.690 align:middle line:84%
Some slight tweak, as
the muscles tighten.

00:40:30.690 --> 00:40:33.300 align:middle line:84%
And now I'm feeling
lighter, different.

00:40:33.300 --> 00:40:35.894 align:middle line:90%
It's hard to place.

00:40:35.894 --> 00:40:39.380 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE CHANTING]

00:40:39.380 --> 00:41:23.960 align:middle line:90%


00:41:23.960 --> 00:41:26.440 align:middle line:84%
>>Guillermo is tuning
us in, sinking us

00:41:26.440 --> 00:41:29.670 align:middle line:90%
into a shared face space.

00:41:29.670 --> 00:41:31.850 align:middle line:90%
The sound is his icaro.

00:41:31.850 --> 00:41:34.410 align:middle line:84%
The first wave of
his bag of tricks

00:41:34.410 --> 00:41:38.670 align:middle line:84%
to pierce the veil that
separates the worlds.

00:41:38.670 --> 00:41:40.090 align:middle line:90%
And viola.

00:41:40.090 --> 00:41:42.740 align:middle line:84%
The curtain is pulled
back and we're smeared

00:41:42.740 --> 00:41:45.460 align:middle line:90%
across the invisible canvas.

00:41:45.460 --> 00:41:48.440 align:middle line:90%
We've arrived.

00:41:48.440 --> 00:41:51.416 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE CHANTING]

00:41:51.416 --> 00:42:05.310 align:middle line:90%


00:42:05.310 --> 00:42:08.830 align:middle line:84%
>>In the Amazonian cosmo
vision, everything on the earth

00:42:08.830 --> 00:42:10.830 align:middle line:90%
has a spirit animating it.

00:42:10.830 --> 00:42:13.440 align:middle line:84%
And the bridge between the
Earth and the spirit world

00:42:13.440 --> 00:42:15.030 align:middle line:90%
is us, the living things.

00:42:15.030 --> 00:42:18.220 align:middle line:90%


00:42:18.220 --> 00:42:22.070 align:middle line:84%
By the moonlight, I can see
the wooden beams of the roof

00:42:22.070 --> 00:42:26.530 align:middle line:84%
shimmering like a vast spider
web, the central pole flashing

00:42:26.530 --> 00:42:30.570 align:middle line:84%
with mythic resonance, like
the world tree of Norse myth,

00:42:30.570 --> 00:42:33.090 align:middle line:84%
connecting the Axis Mundi
with the worlds above.

00:42:33.090 --> 00:42:38.050 align:middle line:90%


00:42:38.050 --> 00:42:41.390 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, around the
circumference of the roof,

00:42:41.390 --> 00:42:43.850 align:middle line:84%
a billion, billion
eyes come into view,

00:42:43.850 --> 00:42:48.790 align:middle line:84%
like a shimmering peacock tale,
all veiled behind a dark lens.

00:42:48.790 --> 00:42:50.430 align:middle line:90%
They drink me in.

00:42:50.430 --> 00:42:54.540 align:middle line:84%
Blink and stare again,
with a reptilian coolness.

00:42:54.540 --> 00:42:57.580 align:middle line:90%
Images warping one into another.

00:42:57.580 --> 00:43:00.040 align:middle line:84%
I feel like I'm
looking into some sort

00:43:00.040 --> 00:43:02.180 align:middle line:90%
of hyper-dimensional mirror.

00:43:02.180 --> 00:43:03.740 align:middle line:84%
And that the thing
on the other side

00:43:03.740 --> 00:43:07.520 align:middle line:84%
is experiencing what it is
to be human through my eyes,

00:43:07.520 --> 00:43:10.700 align:middle line:90%
through all our eyes.

00:43:10.700 --> 00:43:14.080 align:middle line:84%
Sometime in the dream,
Guillermo comes around

00:43:14.080 --> 00:43:17.130 align:middle line:84%
and blows smoke down
our necks and backs.

00:43:17.130 --> 00:43:20.970 align:middle line:84%
He beckons me to lower my
head, not out of respect,

00:43:20.970 --> 00:43:23.410 align:middle line:90%
but to cleanse my crown chakra.

00:43:23.410 --> 00:43:26.060 align:middle line:84%
And his touch has a gentleness
and a collected strength.

00:43:26.060 --> 00:43:31.280 align:middle line:90%


00:43:31.280 --> 00:43:34.040 align:middle line:84%
And then, out of
nowhere, the darkness

00:43:34.040 --> 00:43:38.240 align:middle line:84%
erupts with a thundering
growl, bigger than us all.

00:43:38.240 --> 00:43:41.610 align:middle line:84%
Big enough to hold
the world in its jaws.

00:43:41.610 --> 00:43:46.390 align:middle line:84%
Snakes, crocodiles,
writhing anacondas spirits

00:43:46.390 --> 00:43:49.760 align:middle line:84%
and jaguar eyes imprint
from my subconscious

00:43:49.760 --> 00:43:51.640 align:middle line:90%
under the canvas of the night.

00:43:51.640 --> 00:43:54.730 align:middle line:84%
All my fears spewing
forth with them.

00:43:54.730 --> 00:43:58.500 align:middle line:84%
The ayahuasca makes urgent
rumbles in my belly.

00:43:58.500 --> 00:44:01.910 align:middle line:84%
And as a wave of
nausea washes over me,

00:44:01.910 --> 00:44:05.260 align:middle line:84%
I must have the fortitude
to stand and grope my way

00:44:05.260 --> 00:44:08.380 align:middle line:90%
through the dark to the door.

00:44:08.380 --> 00:44:11.010 align:middle line:90%
Mercifully, it opens.

00:44:11.010 --> 00:44:13.880 align:middle line:84%
And I push it and stumble
out into the night,

00:44:13.880 --> 00:44:17.220 align:middle line:84%
punch drunk with the
spirit of the vine in me,

00:44:17.220 --> 00:44:18.725 align:middle line:90%
threatening to come up quick.

00:44:18.725 --> 00:44:22.365 align:middle line:90%


00:44:22.365 --> 00:44:27.050 align:middle line:84%
The silhouetted jungle is bathed
in a silver spectral light,

00:44:27.050 --> 00:44:30.310 align:middle line:84%
as Peruvian helpers
stationed outside the door

00:44:30.310 --> 00:44:32.185 align:middle line:90%
point me towards the toilets.

00:44:32.185 --> 00:44:34.186 align:middle line:90%
A shimmering ball of light.

00:44:34.186 --> 00:44:36.550 align:middle line:90%
Only 20 meters away.

00:44:36.550 --> 00:44:40.210 align:middle line:84%
It seems to skip in
my field of vision.

00:44:40.210 --> 00:44:42.840 align:middle line:84%
My whole body feels
like it's under water,

00:44:42.840 --> 00:44:45.440 align:middle line:84%
that my consciousness
trying to drive it

00:44:45.440 --> 00:44:48.927 align:middle line:84%
is doing so from very far
away and under challenging

00:44:48.927 --> 00:44:49.510 align:middle line:90%
circumstances.

00:44:49.510 --> 00:44:53.830 align:middle line:90%


00:44:53.830 --> 00:44:58.190 align:middle line:84%
After an eternity on the
path, lost in the trees,

00:44:58.190 --> 00:45:04.310 align:middle line:84%
I finally find my way to the
toilets and an empty cubicle.

00:45:04.310 --> 00:45:08.290 align:middle line:84%
The porcelain bowl
and seat is a miracle.

00:45:08.290 --> 00:45:12.370 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm bathed in the bright,
artificial light, the ayahuasca

00:45:12.370 --> 00:45:16.094 align:middle line:90%
in me judges all is ready.

00:45:16.094 --> 00:45:19.830 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:45:19.830 --> 00:45:23.030 align:middle line:84%
A violent rush of
vomit erupts from me

00:45:23.030 --> 00:45:25.840 align:middle line:84%
and into the basin
next to the toilet.

00:45:25.840 --> 00:45:30.240 align:middle line:84%
And then another, and
another, and another.

00:45:30.240 --> 00:45:34.100 align:middle line:84%
My whole body is gripped
with peristalsis,

00:45:34.100 --> 00:45:38.110 align:middle line:90%
and squeezing out sickness.

00:45:38.110 --> 00:45:39.090 align:middle line:90%
[VOMITING SOUNDS]

00:45:39.090 --> 00:45:43.510 align:middle line:90%


00:45:43.510 --> 00:45:47.340 align:middle line:84%
As I cough and
splutter over the sink,

00:45:47.340 --> 00:45:49.120 align:middle line:84%
and try to hang
on to the shifting

00:45:49.120 --> 00:45:54.070 align:middle line:84%
space-time co-ordinates around
me, a trick of the light

00:45:54.070 --> 00:45:57.900 align:middle line:84%
draws my attention to the warm
sick backed up in the sink.

00:45:57.900 --> 00:46:01.030 align:middle line:90%


00:46:01.030 --> 00:46:06.290 align:middle line:84%
Still bubbling like a fizzy
drink, like ayahuasca cola.

00:46:06.290 --> 00:46:09.890 align:middle line:84%
But it has a curious,
unpleasant film to it,

00:46:09.890 --> 00:46:12.550 align:middle line:90%
like oil rainbows on water.

00:46:12.550 --> 00:46:16.420 align:middle line:84%
The eyes from the other
side of the mirror.

00:46:16.420 --> 00:46:21.920 align:middle line:84%
A magic mirror, perhaps,
created from my ayahuasca vomit.

00:46:21.920 --> 00:46:26.550 align:middle line:84%
And as I look into the magic
mirror, the eyes become spots.

00:46:26.550 --> 00:46:29.700 align:middle line:84%
The spots move with the
shape of a large cat.

00:46:29.700 --> 00:46:31.950 align:middle line:90%
A jaguar stalking the jungle.

00:46:31.950 --> 00:46:35.100 align:middle line:90%


00:46:35.100 --> 00:46:37.820 align:middle line:10%
He stops in front of
a grandfather tree,

00:46:37.820 --> 00:46:41.600 align:middle line:10%
with thick snakes of flowering
ayahuasca vine twining

00:46:41.600 --> 00:46:46.670 align:middle line:10%
around its frame, and looks
back, as if he can see me.

00:46:46.670 --> 00:46:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly pounces, muscle
rippling and claws extended.

00:46:52.010 --> 00:46:54.570 align:middle line:84%
And he shreds the
thick vine into shards,

00:46:54.570 --> 00:46:57.136 align:middle line:84%
and starts nibbling
on the leaves.

00:46:57.136 --> 00:47:00.190 align:middle line:84%
Then he starts tripping
out, rolling around

00:47:00.190 --> 00:47:02.020 align:middle line:90%
with glazed eyes.

00:47:02.020 --> 00:47:03.905 align:middle line:90%
And then he's vomiting, too.

00:47:03.905 --> 00:47:06.830 align:middle line:90%
And I realize it's me.

00:47:06.830 --> 00:47:08.320 align:middle line:90%
Me in the jaguar skin.

00:47:08.320 --> 00:47:12.024 align:middle line:84%
And it me who's vomiting
once again into the sink.

00:47:12.024 --> 00:47:15.330 align:middle line:90%


00:47:15.330 --> 00:47:19.210 align:middle line:84%
I meet my fears,
and they devour me.

00:47:19.210 --> 00:47:24.650 align:middle line:84%
With another roar of the jaguar
god, melts the realization.

00:47:24.650 --> 00:47:27.675 align:middle line:84%
It's the thunder of a
jumbo jet dead overhead.

00:47:27.675 --> 00:47:31.320 align:middle line:84%
The 10 PM flight back to
Lima, back to civilization.

00:47:31.320 --> 00:47:35.700 align:middle line:90%


00:47:35.700 --> 00:47:38.755 align:middle line:84%
And as the hallucinogenic
jungle envelops me,

00:47:38.755 --> 00:47:43.460 align:middle line:84%
I start to wonder if I can
ever come back from this,

00:47:43.460 --> 00:47:47.100 align:middle line:84%
ever return to
civilization as I left it.

00:47:47.100 --> 00:47:50.710 align:middle line:84%
Or if something inside me
now is changed forever.

00:47:50.710 --> 00:47:55.840 align:middle line:84%
And the jaguar is the one who
stalks the world in my skin.

00:47:55.840 --> 00:47:58.810 align:middle line:84%
But there is no
turning back now.

00:47:58.810 --> 00:48:00.610 align:middle line:90%
No off switch.

00:48:00.610 --> 00:48:06.150 align:middle line:84%
Just me alone with the universe,
and the jaguar in the forest.

00:48:06.150 --> 00:48:08.820 align:middle line:84%
Two crazy,
cross-species trippers

00:48:08.820 --> 00:48:13.856 align:middle line:84%
sharing a cosmo vision
that says we are both one.

00:48:13.856 --> 00:48:25.832 align:middle line:90%


00:48:25.832 --> 00:48:29.325 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:48:29.325 --> 00:49:41.310 align:middle line:90%


00:49:41.310 --> 00:49:43.450 align:middle line:10%
Early Friday
morning, Ron Wheelock

00:49:43.450 --> 00:49:46.850 align:middle line:10%
drives me out to his house in
his three-wheeled motorcarro,

00:49:46.850 --> 00:49:49.700 align:middle line:10%
his 3 and 1/2 year old
son, Kato, in the back.

00:49:49.700 --> 00:49:53.380 align:middle line:84%
The wind in his face,
loving every minute of it.

00:49:53.380 --> 00:49:55.860 align:middle line:84%
It all feels so "Easy
Rider," cruising down

00:49:55.860 --> 00:49:59.440 align:middle line:84%
the Iquitos Norta highway in
search of the ultimate mystery.

00:49:59.440 --> 00:50:05.190 align:middle line:90%


00:50:05.190 --> 00:50:08.540 align:middle line:84%
As we get out at Ron's
place, I notice a carved sign

00:50:08.540 --> 00:50:12.170 align:middle line:84%
above the gates, adorned with
wooden flowers that reads

00:50:12.170 --> 00:50:15.030 align:middle line:90%
"La Rosacita," the rosy cross.

00:50:15.030 --> 00:50:17.680 align:middle line:10%
With a little red love heart
dotting the "i" in Rosacita.

00:50:17.680 --> 00:50:20.190 align:middle line:90%


00:50:20.190 --> 00:50:22.440 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's having
young Kato here,

00:50:22.440 --> 00:50:25.980 align:middle line:84%
or the good vibe I get off Ron
and his down to earth manner.

00:50:25.980 --> 00:50:31.910 align:middle line:84%
But this place immediately feels
like home, where the heart is.

00:50:31.910 --> 00:50:34.760 align:middle line:10%
Ron's a weathered
gringo in his early 50s,

00:50:34.760 --> 00:50:37.030 align:middle line:10%
with a worn down,
weather-beaten look,

00:50:37.030 --> 00:50:41.770 align:middle line:10%
like he's just stepped out
of a John Steinbeck novel.

00:50:41.770 --> 00:50:45.100 align:middle line:10%
He's an old-time boy from Kansas
who's always been interested

00:50:45.100 --> 00:50:46.550 align:middle line:10%
in shamanism.

00:50:46.550 --> 00:50:50.640 align:middle line:10%
So one day back in '96,
he decided to come to Peru

00:50:50.640 --> 00:50:54.120 align:middle line:10%
and find himself a teacher.

00:50:54.120 --> 00:50:56.480 align:middle line:84%
The first curandero
he drank with

00:50:56.480 --> 00:51:00.880 align:middle line:84%
was Don Jose Corale Mori,
a renowned local healer

00:51:00.880 --> 00:51:02.520 align:middle line:90%
and a Banco shaman.

00:51:02.520 --> 00:51:06.950 align:middle line:84%
A master of sky, water,
land, and spirits.

00:51:06.950 --> 00:51:09.440 align:middle line:84%
He took him under his wing
and taught him the ways

00:51:09.440 --> 00:51:11.080 align:middle line:90%
of the jungle medicine.

00:51:11.080 --> 00:51:14.640 align:middle line:84%
And now, Ron practices
as the gringo shaman

00:51:14.640 --> 00:51:18.554 align:middle line:84%
to a growing clientele
of Western seekers.

00:51:18.554 --> 00:51:21.482 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE CHANTING]

00:51:21.482 --> 00:51:24.300 align:middle line:90%


00:51:24.300 --> 00:51:27.180 align:middle line:84%
>>Anybody's done much work
with ayahuasca will tell you.

00:51:27.180 --> 00:51:29.140 align:middle line:84%
We don't choose to
drink ayahuasca.

00:51:29.140 --> 00:51:31.380 align:middle line:90%
She chooses us.

00:51:31.380 --> 00:51:33.750 align:middle line:90%
And I find that very true.

00:51:33.750 --> 00:51:37.070 align:middle line:84%
So, you know, there's
hallucinogenic plants

00:51:37.070 --> 00:51:38.890 align:middle line:90%
