And it is it.

01:12:50.660 --> 01:12:57.980 align:middle line:84%
And on, and on, and on in
perfect, radiating super-union.

01:12:57.980 --> 01:12:59.310 align:middle line:90%
But what the fuck is it?

01:12:59.310 --> 01:13:09.270 align:middle line:90%


01:13:09.270 --> 01:13:12.756 align:middle line:90%
[NATIVE SINGING]

01:13:12.756 --> 01:14:03.500 align:middle line:90%


01:14:03.500 --> 01:14:06.850 align:middle line:84%
Ollantaytambo is an ancient
Inca fortress temple,

01:14:06.850 --> 01:14:10.500 align:middle line:84%
nestled in the Urubamba
valley, surrounded on all sides

01:14:10.500 --> 01:14:15.020 align:middle line:84%
by languid mountains that
break against the sky.

01:14:15.020 --> 01:14:17.130 align:middle line:10%
The base of the
mountains are strewn

01:14:17.130 --> 01:14:20.550 align:middle line:10%
with plantation terraces,
made from finely cut stones,

01:14:20.550 --> 01:14:24.450 align:middle line:10%
with ruined forts, temples,
and battlements further up

01:14:24.450 --> 01:14:27.650 align:middle line:10%
the incline that hint at the
mountain civilization that

01:14:27.650 --> 01:14:31.930 align:middle line:10%
existed here in its prime,
almost 3,000 meters above sea

01:14:31.930 --> 01:14:34.680 align:middle line:10%
level.

01:14:34.680 --> 01:14:38.170 align:middle line:84%
Some ruins are perched on
such isolated juts of rock

01:14:38.170 --> 01:14:41.650 align:middle line:84%
that it seems as if they must
have sprouted here organically.

01:14:41.650 --> 01:14:43.910 align:middle line:84%
For surely no human
hand could build them

01:14:43.910 --> 01:14:47.150 align:middle line:84%
on the hips of these
towering giants.

01:14:47.150 --> 01:14:50.050 align:middle line:90%
But the Incas did.

01:14:50.050 --> 01:14:52.590 align:middle line:10%
By the time the Spanish
conquistadors sacked

01:14:52.590 --> 01:14:57.770 align:middle line:10%
Cuzco in 1535, Maco Inca,
the emperor of the time,

01:14:57.770 --> 01:15:00.350 align:middle line:10%
retreated to
Ollantaytambo, where

01:15:00.350 --> 01:15:02.850 align:middle line:10%
he used its strategic
location, including

01:15:02.850 --> 01:15:05.280 align:middle line:10%
the fortified gates
and guard houses

01:15:05.280 --> 01:15:08.270 align:middle line:10%
and the naturally state
slopes and vertical walls,

01:15:08.270 --> 01:15:11.048 align:middle line:10%
to temporarily hold back
the Spanish invaders.

01:15:11.048 --> 01:15:14.120 align:middle line:90%


01:15:14.120 --> 01:15:18.460 align:middle line:84%
500 years later, the
invaders are unstoppable,

01:15:18.460 --> 01:15:22.020 align:middle line:84%
decked out with sun hats,
video cameras, water bottles

01:15:22.020 --> 01:15:23.950 align:middle line:90%
and backpacks.

01:15:23.950 --> 01:15:26.980 align:middle line:84%
Constant streams of
touristos pile out

01:15:26.980 --> 01:15:29.730 align:middle line:84%
of a fleet of super-size
tall buses that

01:15:29.730 --> 01:15:33.350 align:middle line:90%
have pulled up in the car park.

01:15:33.350 --> 01:15:35.490 align:middle line:10%
There must be hundreds
of people here,

01:15:35.490 --> 01:15:38.280 align:middle line:10%
all desperately looking for some
relief from the late morning

01:15:38.280 --> 01:15:41.220 align:middle line:10%
sun, studying their
maps and guide books

01:15:41.220 --> 01:15:44.700 align:middle line:10%
as they prepare to brave the
cobblestone street gauntlet,

01:15:44.700 --> 01:15:47.580 align:middle line:10%
past all the handicraft
sellers, and head down

01:15:47.580 --> 01:15:51.670 align:middle line:10%
towards the main section of town
to really get their ruins on.

01:15:51.670 --> 01:15:54.960 align:middle line:90%


01:15:54.960 --> 01:15:57.780 align:middle line:10%
I'm here with Kevin
Furnas, the American shaman

01:15:57.780 --> 01:16:00.320 align:middle line:10%
I met back in Iquitos
at the conference,

01:16:00.320 --> 01:16:04.080 align:middle line:10%
and two of his apprentices,
Mira and Ricardo,

01:16:04.080 --> 01:16:07.230 align:middle line:10%
a Peruvian in his
40s with sharp eyes,

01:16:07.230 --> 01:16:12.750 align:middle line:10%
bushy black eyebrows, and
puffy cheeks like a puma.

01:16:12.750 --> 01:16:15.390 align:middle line:90%
So, what's the plan?

01:16:15.390 --> 01:16:18.780 align:middle line:84%
Well, I thought we'd avoid
the usual tourist traps down

01:16:18.780 --> 01:16:21.570 align:middle line:84%
by the terraces, in
the Temple of the Sun,

01:16:21.570 --> 01:16:24.870 align:middle line:84%
and climb old Pinkuylluna
Hill up here, Kevin says.

01:16:24.870 --> 01:16:28.020 align:middle line:90%


01:16:28.020 --> 01:16:31.010 align:middle line:84%
Look, can you see
the face, he cries,

01:16:31.010 --> 01:16:32.787 align:middle line:84%
pointing towards the
side of the mountain.

01:16:32.787 --> 01:16:35.650 align:middle line:90%


01:16:35.650 --> 01:16:39.840 align:middle line:84%
The locals say we Viracocha,
their creator god.

01:16:39.840 --> 01:16:42.060 align:middle line:84%
He came down to earth
on a little island

01:16:42.060 --> 01:16:46.580 align:middle line:84%
in the center of Lake Titicaca,
called the Island of the Sun.

01:16:46.580 --> 01:16:49.860 align:middle line:84%
And everywhere he
walked, he created form,

01:16:49.860 --> 01:16:53.010 align:middle line:84%
imbuing everything
with his essence.

01:16:53.010 --> 01:16:56.100 align:middle line:84%
He made humans from the clay,
and they built the temples

01:16:56.100 --> 01:16:59.220 align:middle line:84%
here, that trace the
path of the sky god

01:16:59.220 --> 01:17:01.510 align:middle line:84%
as he walked across the
mountains to the sea

01:17:01.510 --> 01:17:06.460 align:middle line:84%
and back again, creating
the sacred valley.

01:17:06.460 --> 01:17:08.580 align:middle line:84%
I've got to tell
you, like [SIGHS] I

01:17:08.580 --> 01:17:11.000 align:middle line:84%
can feel the energy
of the mountain.

01:17:11.000 --> 01:17:12.870 align:middle line:84%
I can't believe
how sensitive I've

01:17:12.870 --> 01:17:16.230 align:middle line:84%
become to energy itself
in these last few weeks,

01:17:16.230 --> 01:17:18.700 align:middle line:90%
ever since I left the jungle.

01:17:18.700 --> 01:17:20.200 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:17:20.200 --> 01:17:21.930 align:middle line:90%
Well, you know.

01:17:21.930 --> 01:17:25.210 align:middle line:84%
All the visionary plant is
doing is taking the filters

01:17:25.210 --> 01:17:30.017 align:middle line:84%
off the chakras, so you can
see directly, Kevin begins.

01:17:30.017 --> 01:17:31.840 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, it's not
ayahuasca visions.

01:17:31.840 --> 01:17:33.580 align:middle line:84%
